re joy, and I want our athletes to feel the support of the entire Jamaica.\", \"from\": 282, \"to\": 394, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 386, \"end\": 393, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"score\": 0.9999999996261977, \"rank\": 3.2500019698764047e-10, \"text\": \"Jamaica\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The Olympics\", \"from\": 283, \"to\": 295}, {\"ngram\": \"a moment\", \"from\": 306, \"to\": 314}, {\"ngram\": \"pure joy\", \"from\": 318, \"to\": 326}, {\"ngram\": \"our athletes\", \"from\": 339, \"to\": 351}, {\"ngram\": \"the support\", \"from\": 360, \"to\": 371}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This song celebrates their dedication and hard work.\", \"from\": 395, \"to\": 447, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"This song\", \"from\": 395, \"to\": 404}, {\"ngram\": \"their dedication\", \"from\": 416, \"to\": 432}, {\"ngram\": \"hard work\", \"from\": 437, \"to\": 446}]}, {\"sentence\": \"I produced it to encourage them to believe and dream big when they 'Guh Fi Gold and Glory' knowing they have infinite support,\\\" said Bolt.\", \"from\": 448, \"to\": 586, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Guh Fi Gold\", \"from\": 516, \"to\": 527}, {\"ngram\": \"Glory\", \"from\": 532, \"to\": 537}, {\"ngram\": \"infinite support\", \"from\": 557, \"to\": 573}, {\"ngram\": \"Bolt\", \"from\": 581, \"to\": 585}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As a part of the Guh Fi Gold and Glory campaign, the song is set to unite the cheers of Jamaicans worldwide.\", \"from\": 588, \"to\": 696, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 676, \"end\": 685, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9999999999949978, \"rank\": 3.5742457643137955e-12, \"text\": \"Jamaicans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"a part\", \"from\": 591, \"to\": 597}, {\"ngram\": \"the Guh Fi Gold and Glory campaign\", \"from\": 601, \"to\": 635}, {\"ngram\": \"the song\", \"from\": 637, \"to\": 645}, {\"ngram\": \"the cheers\", \"from\": 662, \"to\": 672}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The song features collaborations with musical sensations Busy Signal and Shaneil Muir to amplify the spirit of Jamaicans everywhere.\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 829, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 808, \"end\": 817, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"score\": 0.9999999999949978, \"rank\": 3.5742457643137955e-12, \"text\": \"Jamaicans\", \"types\": [\"Q41710\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaicans\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The song\", \"from\": 697, \"to\": 705}, {\"ngram\": \"collaborations\", \"from\": 715, \"to\": 729}, {\"ngram\": \"musical sensations\", \"from\": 735, \"to\": 753}, {\"ngram\": \"Signal\", \"from\": 759, \"to\": 765}, {\"ngram\": \"Shaneil Muir\", \"from\": 770, \"to\": 782}, {\"ngram\": \"the spirit\", \"from\": 794, \"to\": 804}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Busy Signal, known for headlining the Red Stripe Independence songBig Up Jamaica, released in 2022, also brings his signature energy to this project.\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 980, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Busy Signal\", \"from\": 831, \"to\": 842}, {\"ngram\": \"the Red Stripe Independence\", \"from\": 865, \"to\": 892}, {\"ngram\": \"his signature energy\", \"from\": 943, \"to\": 963}, {\"ngram\": \"this project\", \"from\": 967, \"to\": 979}]}, {\"sentence\": \"\\\"There is no better way to celebrate the Paris 2024 Olympic Games than with Usain capturing the infectious beat of dancehall, the inspired spirit of our people, and our aspiration to be the greatest versions of humanity.\", \"from\": 982, \"to\": 1202, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"no better way\", \"from\": 992, \"to\": 1005}, {\"ngram\": \"the Paris\", \"from\": 1019, \"to\": 1028}, {\"ngram\": \"2024 Olympic Games\", \"from\": 1029, \"to\": 1047}, {\"ngram\": \"Usain\", \"from\": 1058, \"to\": 1063}, {\"ngram\": \"the infectious beat\", \"from\": 1074, \"to\": 1093}, {\"ngram\": \"dancehall\", \"from\": 1097, \"to\": 1106}, {\"ngram\": \"the inspired spirit\", \"from\": 1108, \"to\": 1127}, {\"ngram\": \"our people\", \"from\": 1131, \"to\": 1141}, {\"ngram\": \"our aspiration\", \"from\": 1147, \"to\": 1161}, {\"ngram\": \"the greatest versions\", \"from\": 1168, \"to\": 1189}, {\"ngram\": \"humanity\", \"from\": 1193, \"to\": 1201}]}, {\"sentence\": \"It's born and bred in our culture, and when the JOA [Jamaica Olympic Association] and Red Stripe teamed up with Bolt it can only be electrifying\\u2026\\\" shared JOA President Christopher Samuda.\", \"from\": 1203, \"to\": 1390, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1251, \"end\": 1254, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newspaper_Preservation_Act_of_1970\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"JOA\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newspaper_Preservation_Act_of_1970\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Newspaper_Preservation_Act_of_1970\"}, {\"begin\": 1256, \"end\": 1283, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica_Olympic_Association\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Jamaica Olympic Association\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica_Olympic_Association\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Jamaica_Olympic_Association\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"our culture\", \"from\": 1225, \"to\": 1236}, {\"ngram\": \"Red Stripe\", \"from\": 1289, \"to\": 1299}, {\"ngram\": \"Bolt\", \"from\": 1315, \"to\": 1319}]}, {\"sentence\": \"On June 2, at the National Stadium, Jamaicans witnessed a preview of the talents bound for Paris between July 26 and August 11, 2024.\", \"from\": 1392, \"to\": 1525, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1428, \"end\": 1437, \"title\": \"h